4. Core Academic Entities

The system enforces strict separation between academic objects.

⸻

Course

A course represents an academic topic offered by a department.

Fields:

Department
Course Number
Course Name
Description
Credit Hours
Difficulty Rating

Example

Department: CS
Course Number: 2110
Course Name: Design of Algorithms

Constraints

• Course number must be numeric
• Course name must be text
• Course number and course name must be separate fields
• Course numbers must be unique within a department

⸻

Section

A section represents a specific offering of a course.

Fields

Course
Section Code
Instructor
Meeting Days
Start Time
End Time
Location
CRN

Example

CS 2110
Section A
Instructor: Dr Smith
Days: Monday Wednesday
Time: 1:00PM – 2:30PM

Constraints

• Course must be selected from existing course records
• Instructor must be selected from existing instructor records
• Section code must be text
• CRN must be unique

⸻

Instructor

Represents a professor or lecturer.

Fields

Name
Department
Rating
Teaching Style

Constraints

• Instructor names must be unique
• Instructors must exist before they can be assigned to sections

⸻

5. Admin System

TechPath includes a strict administrative interface responsible for maintaining all academic data.

Students cannot modify academic records.

Admins maintain all course structures and relationships.

⸻

Admin Capabilities

Admins can perform CRUD operations on the following objects:

Courses
Sections
Instructors
Prerequisites
Reviews (delete only)

Admins can view but not modify student schedules.

⸻

Admin Object Assignment Rules

All relational objects must be selected from existing records using dropdown selectors.

Examples of valid assignment:

Instructor: selected from instructor list

Course: selected from course list

Examples of invalid assignment:

Typing instructor name manually
Typing prerequisite course manually

⸻

Admin Interface Sections

Admin Dashboard

Courses
Sections
Instructors
Prerequisites
Reviews

⸻

Course Creation (Admin)

Required Fields

Department
Course Number
Course Name
Description
Credit Hours
Difficulty Rating

Constraints

Department must be selected from predefined department list

Course Number must be numeric

Course Name must be text

Duplicate department + course number combinations are not allowed

⸻

Section Creation (Admin)

Required Fields

Course
Section Code
Instructor
Meeting Days
Start Time
End Time
Location
CRN

Constraints

Instructor must be selected from instructor list

Course must be selected from course list

CRN must be unique

⸻

Time Constraints

Class times follow strict rules.

Time increments are limited to 15 minute intervals.

Valid schedule time range

7:00 AM through 9:00 PM

Examples of valid times

7:00
7:15
7:30
7:45
8:00

Examples of invalid times

6:30
9:30 PM

Classes cannot begin before 7:00 AM and cannot end after 9:00 PM.

⸻

Day Constraints

Sections may only meet on the following days

Monday
Tuesday
Wednesday
Thursday
Friday

Days must be stored as constrained enumerations.

⸻

Prerequisite Assignment

Admins assign prerequisites for courses.

Each prerequisite must reference an existing course.

Multiple prerequisites are allowed.

Example

Course: CS 2110
Prerequisite: CS 1332

⸻

