9. Semester Schedule Builder

Users can create multiple schedules.

Examples

Fall 2025
Spring 2026
Fall 2026

⸻

Schedule Page Layout

Two main sections exist

Sidebar
Calendar View

⸻

Sidebar

The sidebar lists classes currently in the schedule.

Each class card displays

Course code
Course name
Section
Instructor
Meeting time

Clicking a class card navigates to the course detail page.

⸻

Calendar View

The calendar displays weekly course blocks.

Columns represent weekdays

Monday
Tuesday
Wednesday
Thursday
Friday

Rows represent time of day.

The calendar begins at 7:00 AM and ends at 9:00 PM.

Each row represents a 15 minute interval.

Courses appear as blocks spanning their scheduled time.

Clicking a calendar block opens the course page in a new tab.

⸻

Schedule Editing

Users may remove classes from schedules.

Removal requires confirmation.

⸻

Credit Hour Display

The sidebar displays the total credit hours for the schedule.

⸻

10. Career Planner

The Career Planner allows students to organize semester schedules into a long-term academic plan.

Example

Computer Science Degree Plan

⸻

Career Structure

A career contains ordered semester schedules.

Example

Fall 2025
Spring 2026
Fall 2026
Spring 2027

⸻

Drag and Drop

Users can drag schedules to reorder them.

Users can also drag courses between schedules.

⸻

Prerequisite Validation

When a course appears before its prerequisite, the system detects a violation.

Violating courses are highlighted in red.

A warning notification is displayed.

⸻

Conflict Resolution

If a user moves a course to an invalid semester, a prompt appears.

The prompt offers to move the course to an eligible semester where prerequisites are satisfied.

If no eligible semester exists, the system displays

No eligible schedules available.

⸻

